  "blackMoment": {
    "description": "Just after the first time physical intimacy becomes mutual, chosen vulnerability rather than crisis response, the truth surfaces: Lirien's mission was never merely surveillance, the contract was never suspended, and Kaelith's blood lives inside the binding that requires her heartbeat to cease. The revelation retroactively poisons every trust beat — the Oathbrand removal, the kiss, the sex, the shared magic — by making them look like the most sophisticated grooming operation Kaelith has ever endured. Lirien, meanwhile, is forced to confront that the Court built her so thoroughly as a weapon that even the love she thought might be choice can be interpreted as a side effect of proximity and blood-binding.",
    "triggerEvent": "A Seep interception during an escalating Pallor tear exposes the contract text and blood-binding proof at the exact moment Kaelith and Lirien are moving from private surrender into open strategic partnership, collapsing romance and fantasy trust simultaneously.",
    "emotionalNadir": "Kaelith believes the one person who saw her clearly only stayed close because institutions always need her alive until they are ready to use or erase her; Lirien believes she has never once acted outside the architecture that made her, and that loving Kaelith may only prove how total her conditioning is. Reunion appears emotionally and strategically irrecoverable."
  },
